<div  lang="en">

<p nodeIndex="66">The above video is one of my favorite presentations I&rsquo;ve given in 2009, an opening keynote at the last <a id="aptureLink_loYdDE39mN" href="http://2009.sf.wordcamp.org/" nodeIndex="1428">San Francisco WordCamp</a>, titled &ldquo;How to Blog without Killing Yourself&rdquo;. More than 700 people from 32 countries were in attendance, which made for a wonderful experience.</p>
<p nodeIndex="67">The original title was &ldquo;Scalable Blogging Behaviors: How to Grow from 1 to 1,000,000 Readers&rdquo; and the content did not change.</p>
<p nodeIndex="68">In the above presentation, including detailed screenshots, I cover&hellip;<span id="more-1955" nodeIndex="1429"></span></p>
<ul nodeIndex="70"><li nodeIndex="69">Why I blog</li>
<li nodeIndex="71">How I blog and select best practices</li>
<li nodeIndex="72">Frequency and tools &mdash; best times and days to post</li>
<li nodeIndex="73">Blogging myths and how to harness data for better results</li>
<li nodeIndex="74">Testing design and surprising findings that can be copied</li>
<li nodeIndex="75">How I address comments and community building</li>
<li nodeIndex="76">How I write and research for good social media response</li>
<li nodeIndex="77">20 minutes of audience Q&amp;A on Twitter, branding, outsourcing, and much more</li>
</ul><p nodeIndex="78">I hope you enjoy it as much as I enjoyed giving it.</p>
